========================================================
PROMPT EXAMPLE — Option 1: Map All Nodes in One Call
========================================================

This file shows a concrete example of the prompt sent to the LLM under
Option 1 (option: 1 in LLM_mapping_RA.yml). In this mode, RAMD asks the
LLM to assign a Reference Architecture component to every node in the
graph in a single request.

The prompt is constructed by prompts.build_option1_prompt() and includes:
  - The graph structure (node names + undirected edges)
  - RA component names with their textual descriptions (if use_ra_descriptions: true)
  - Few-shot examples drawn from the same RA domain (if fewshot_learning: true)
  - Constraint feedback from the previous iteration (if check_RA_constraints: true)
  - A task instruction specifying the required JSON output schema

------------------------------------------------------------
SYSTEM PROMPT
------------------------------------------------------------
You are an expert software architect. Your task is to map nodes in an AADL
architecture graph to components in a reference architecture. You MUST output
ONLY a single valid JSON object, without any markdown formatting, code fences,
or explanations.

